angstd.ui
Class WorkspaceManager

java.lang.Object
  angstd.ui.WorkspaceManager

public class WorkspaceManager
extends java.lang.Object

The WorkspaceManager is the interface to all workspace related classes.

This class provides methods for workspace manipulation and communication with the ViewHandler. Also some helper methods are provided s well as a method to get a grip on the selectionManager.

This class follows the singleton pattern and should be used for any manipulations of the workspace.

Author:
Andreas Held

addViewToWorkspace

public void addViewToWorkspace(View view,
                               ProjectElement project)
Adds the new view to the specified project within the Workspace. If the project is null, the currently active project is taken. If there are no projects in the workspace anymore, e.g. after deletion the default project is added again.

Parameters:
view - the view to add
project - the project to which the view should be added

removeFromAngstd

public void removeFromAngstd(WorkspaceElement element)
Gets only called when view elements are deleted by the workspace context menu option "delete". In a first step all views are deleted from the workspace and in a second step they are also removed from the ViewHandler. Do not call this method from within the ViewHandler or else you will get to an infinite loop. If you want to clean the workspace from within the ViewHandler, e.g. because a view was closed use removeViewFromWorkspace().

Parameters:
element - the element to be deleted (e.g. project, category, view)

removeViewFromWorkspace

public void removeViewFromWorkspace(ViewInfo viewInfo)
Method to remove views from the workspace based on its viewInfo

Parameters:
viewInfo - the viewInfo describing the view which is about to be deleted
